Stocks Rebound; Bank Shares Lead FTSE 100 Index Gains as ECB Buys Bonds

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-08-08T07:27:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/stocks-rebound-bank-shares-lead-ftse-100-index-gains-as-ecb-buys-bonds.html
U.K. stocks rebounded, lead by a
rally among bank shares. The benchmark FTSE 100 Index climbed
32.97, or 0.6 percent, to 5,279.96 as of 8:27 a.m. in  London .
The gauge had fallen as much as 1.3 percent during the first 20
minutes of trading today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
